── Description ─────────────────────────────────────────
Fix spelling mistakes reported by `typos` (see https://gitlab.com/diffinder/dfmain/-/merge_requests/5064)

This is a brute force typo fix which. Just blindly merging this will likely cause issues so we'll have to think about how we actually merge this. It's also . Here's Claude's suggestions as a starting point:

> SQL — needs migration or revert
>
> 1. Migration constraint name changed (20230125_allow_longer_texts.sql): DROP CONSTRAINT ledger_accounting_fault_description_ser\_... was changed to ..._set_.... The constraint in production is named _ser_. This migration has already run — this change makes the file wrong.
> 2. Two migration files renamed:
>
> - 20230325_add_task_uuid_to_eamil_data.sql → ..._email_...
> - 20260206_add_indenpendence_confirmation\_... → ..._independence_...
>
> Migration runners use filenames as identifiers. Renaming applied migrations will cause them to be seen as new unapplied migrations and re-run.
>
> ---
>
> Serde/serialized data — runtime breaks on old persisted data
>
> These renames change the string representation in JSON/messages. Existing persisted records or in-flight messages will fail to deserialize:
>
> | Changed | In |
> |---------|----|
> | "ChangedDimentionName" → "ChangedDimensionName" | UnitsMergeWarning (serde tagged enum) |
> | "Auxilliary" → "Auxiliary" | RiskAssessmentCategory string serialization, TS/Rust stores |
> | "uncommited_changes" → "uncommitted_changes" | LedgerVersion JSON + Zod schema |
> | "corproate_id" → "corporate_id" | ExportMetadata serde field |
> | "Splitted{n}" → "Split{n}" | EntryModification Display/string form |
>
> ---
>
> TypeScript — will fail to compile if there are other importers
>
> These are named exports that were renamed. The diff updated the known usages, but any file not caught will break:
>
> - accountingSoftwares → accountingSoftware (cases.type.ts)
> - NotificiationView → NotificationView (notifications.ts)
> - AcceptenceCriteriaMetadata → AcceptanceCriteriaMetadata (acceptance.type.ts)
> - translateOperaitonAndUnknown → translateOperationAndUnknown (helpers.ts)
> - infinteScroll → infiniteScroll (infinite_scroll.ts)
> - getRiskAssesmentSummaryTextInputs → getRiskAssessmentSummaryTextInputs (material-accounts.ts)
>
> Running pnpm --filter audit check should surface any missed importers.

